            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1292413506,
            "creation_date": 1292413506,
            "body": "<p>You can use Ant for this: <a href=\"http://ant.apache.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://ant.apache.org/<\/a><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 4449522,
            "question_id": 4449502
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e384f5d19d179fbbe79e58bea20b2cb6?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 47795,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 141688,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/141688/rlovtang",
                "reputation": 5070,
                "display_name": "rlovtang",
                "accept_rate": 45
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 2.5",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1292414484,
            "creation_date": 1292413752,
            "body": "<p>A build tool, like <a href=\"http://gradle.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Gradle<\/a> is perfect for this.<\/p>\n\n<p>See the <a href=\"http://gradle.org/tutorial_java_projects.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">tutorial for java projects<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n<p>Create a build.gradle file, where you use the <a href=\"http://gradle.org/java_plugin.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">java plugin<\/a>:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>apply plugin: 'java'\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>You either need to move your java files to src/main/java, or specify the source folder in build.gradle, something like this:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>sourceSets {\n    main {\n        java {\n            srcDir 'src/java'\n        }\n        resources {\n            srcDir 'src/resources'\n        }\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Then run 'gradle jar'<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 4449557,
            "question_id": 4449502,
            "last_edit_date": 1292414484
        }
    ],
